  "prompt": "What universities does W&T offshore recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "W&T Offshore, like many companies in the oil and gas industry, typically recruits new graduates from a variety of universities, especially those with strong engineering programs and relevant disciplines. While the specific universities may vary over time and by location, they often include:\n\n1. **University of Houston**\n2. **Texas A&M University**\n3. **University of Texas at Austin**\n4. **Louisiana State University (LSU)**\n5. **Colorado School of Mines**\n6. **University of California, Berkeley**\n\nAs for majors, W&T Offshore primarily looks for candidates in the following areas:\n\n1. **Petroleum Engineering**\n2. **Mechanical Engineering**\n3. **Chemical Engineering**\n4. **Civil Engineering**\n5. **Geology or Geosciences**\n6. **Environmental Engineering**\n7. **Electrical Engineering**\n\nIn addition to these engineering and science-focused disciplines, the company may also seek candidates with backgrounds in business or finance for roles related to management, finance, or corporate operations.\n\nTo get the most accurate and current information, it's advisable to check W&T Offshore's official careers page or reach out to their HR department directly, as recruitment practices can change over time.",
